$answer = $x - (( 2.35 * $S ) / ( sqrt(3) ));

BEGIN_TEXT
	
The torque provided from 4 motors has a mean of \($x\) \(Nm\) and a standard deviation of \($S\) \(Nm\). With 90% confidence, what is the minimum expected mean torque (in \(Nm\)) of all motors?

$PAR

\{ ans_rule(35) \}
 
END_TEXT

